  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PARC DEC Food Security and Livelihoods Recovery for Crisis-Affected Families in Gaza</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) Resuming and improve food production patterns for vulnerable farmers (conflict-affected farmers, owners of open fields (196 dunums, greenhouses (88 dunums), small scale farmer owners of (24) poultry farms for (female and male), totally and partially damaged  in Rafah. 2) Protection and support affected agricultural infrastructure of agricultural roads (8 km), water wells (4 wells), water carriers (4.5 km) and water reservoir(1) in Rafah Governorate. 3) Emergency distribution of food baskets (415 families for two month on weekly bases) to affected households in  Rafah Governorate. 4) Temporarily create job opportunities ( 864 labour in favour of 60 workers) for jobless agricultural workers. (Cash for work)</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">20 IDPs are able to support their families through access to short term employment in labouring on agricultural rehabilitation activities, including irrigation and road rehabilitation over a combined total of 504 working days. 415 IDPs from the most vulnerable families supported through periods of short term food shortage, through the provision of  food basket distributions on a twice-monthly basis over 3 months (2490 baskets total).43 small scale farms (constituting family 301 members) demonstrate improved food security through the rehabilitation open field farms and greenhouses.12 small scale poultry farms (constituting 84 family members) demonstrate improved food security through rehabilitation of facilities and restocking. 80 farmers (of 560 family members) demonstrate improved food security and through the cultivation of 200 dunums of rehabilitated land and associated infrastructure, including 2km of rural roads and 2km of irrigation channels.</narrative>
  </description>
